data.enText: a large covered structure with rows of seats for people to watch sports events

data.chText: 比赛时大看台上座无虚席。
data.enText: The game was played to a packed grandstand.

data.chText: 从她的住所望去，我们把整个庆祝活动尽收眼底。
data.enText: From her house, we had a grandstand view (= very good view) of the celebrations.

tr: a stand at a racecourse or stadium consisting of tiers with rows of individual seats that are under a protective roof
the audience at a stadium or racetrack
perform ostentatiously in order to impress the audience and with an eye to the applause
example: She never misses a chance to grandstand

value.def: A grandstand is a covered stand with rows of seats for people to sit on at sporting events.
